720000f.title: Manhattan: Gay Street - Christopher Street
720000f.text:
19 to 7 Gay Street, east side, south from Christopher
Street to Waverly Place, showing private dwellings in
a quaint sector of Greenwich Village.
NEG ~S269
1940
Alexander Alland, photo
NO REPRODUCSIONS

718778f-a.title: Manhattan: Christopher Street - Gay Street
718778f-a.text:
16, 18-20, 22, 24 Christopher Street, south side, adjoining
and west of the west corner of Gay Street, west of Greenwich Ave
Nos. 16, 18, and 20 are old frame houses faced with brick. 18-2
are especially prized for their quaintness.
June 4, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPPODUCTIONS.
V26 E27

718779f-b.title: Manhattan: Christopher Street - Gay Street
718779f-b.text:
(1)
22, 20-18, 16, 14 Christopher Street, south side, adjoining
and at the west corner of Gay Street, and east: a good view of
the old frame houses, faced with brick, at Nos. 20-18 and 16.
The dormer windows are an unusual type.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 569.
